[STEP PROMPTING]---->
You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
The current maze looks like this:

agent empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left', 'right'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: right

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to left cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left

You need to solve a 6x9 maze. The maze contains objects like a 'key', a 'hidden key', a 'ladder', a 'tube', and a 'door'. Follow these steps to complete the task:

	•	First, use the tube to go downstairs.
	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
You have moved to right cell.
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.

	•	Find both the regular and hidden keys. You must collect both before proceeding.
	•	After collecting both keys, use the ladder to go back upstairs.
	•	Only after collecting both keys can you unlock the door upstairs.
You will be given a description of the maze at each step. You can move in four directions: 'left', 'right', 'up', or 'down'. Focus on using objects (tube, ladder, door) correctly at the right time.
Information: You cannot take 'down' action in this state as you are facing a wall. Please choose another action.The following actions are feasible in this state: ['right', 'left'].
The current maze looks like this:

empty empty empty empty empty empty empty empty door
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
wall wall wall wall ladder wall tube wall wall
key empty hidden_key empty empty wall tube wall wall
empty empty empty empty empty empty empty agent empty


What is the next action that the agent should take? Only choose from the list of available actions. Do not include anything else in your response. For example, if you choose 'up', then only write 'up' in your response.
You have already tried the following actions: down. Please choose another action.

LLM Response: left
Done: False
